==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Raker
<hw>Rak"er</hw> <pr>(r⟦amac⟧k"⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See 1st
<er>Rake</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who, or that which,
rakes</def>; as: <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A person who uses a rake.</def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>A machine for raking grain or hay by horse or other
power.</def> <sd>(c)</sd> <def>A gun so placed as to rake an enemy's
ship.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>See <cref>Gill rakers</cref>,
under 1st <er>Gill</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rakery</ent>⟦br⟧
